    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - POWER CYLINDERS - Installation</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Piston and Ring Assembly</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, note the engine serial number (stamped on the crankcase pad, left
                        side rear of the crankcase) and piston part number (stamped on the piston crown). Multiple
                        pistons are available for service applications. Do not install pistons having different part
                        numbers.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Some engines have pistons with greater mass, depending on engine serial number. Inertia values
                        of the flywheel, flexplate, and vibration damper must compliment the pistons mass. Contact your
                        International dealer for details.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure the connecting rods and pistons are assembled correctly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650720" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd04/D0423.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 276. Correct position of installed connecting rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Longer leg of connecting rod (cam side)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CAM V8 stamp on cam side of piston crown</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Assemble the piston rings, piston, and connecting rod as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect piston to connecting rod as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Lubricate connecting rod piston pin bore, piston pin bore, and piston pin with clean
                        engine oil.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Orient the longer leg of the connecting rod with the side of the piston bearing the
                        CAM V8 stamped in its crown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f2650721" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figd04/D0402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                        <caption>Figure 277. Piston pin retaining ring</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Use pliers to install retaining ring at one end of piston pin bore.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Slide piston pin through bored holes, stopping at installed retaining ring.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Use pliers to install second retaining ring.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the piston pin end clearance .</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use Piston Ring Expansion Pliers to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2350715">install piston rings onto piston</hotlnk>
                    as follows:
                </para>
                <figure id="f2650722" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd04/D0426.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 278. Piston ring locations</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Top compression ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Intermediate compression ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Oil control ring</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f2650723" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd04/D0401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 279. Rings in piston</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring Expansion Pliers</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring (top compression shown)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install expansion spring component of two piece oil control ring into bottom piston
                        groove.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install oil scraper component of two piece oil control ring over expansion spring.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f2650724" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figd04/D0414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                        <caption>Figure 280. Piston ring identification marks (top ring shown)</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Identification mark</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f2350716">Install intermediate ring into middle piston groove</hotlnk>. The
                        intermediate ring is identified by two 'OO' marks located on the top surface of the ring.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f2350715">Install compression ring into top piston groove</hotlnk>. The
                        compression ring is identified by the 'O' mark located on the top surface of the ring. Make sure
                        the ring is installed with the identification mark facing up.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install intermediate and top compression rings with their identification marks facing up
                    (to top of piston). Space ring gaps approximately 120&#176; apart after ring installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
